Honored Circle</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaedan>Gaedan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#000000>(6/23/03 8:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.4th-wall.net/images/pint.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dirty tricks change</span><hr size=1> The main points have been covered.  I feel that the new Tricks has more potential, but more room to fail as well, resists, dice going against you, etc.  My main gripe with DT is that to do its potential, you have to be a mez breaker: not like before where you could just &quot;fire and forget&quot; and &quot;ghetto mez&quot; a melee or an archer.<br>
<br>
The other gripe I guess is that it has no effect on casters; but this is kind of an ignorant statement because if you're hitting a caster with dirty tricks, you're already in melee range and interrupting them (and hopefully killing them).  But it doesn't really give any advantage to use against a caster, whereas TW and Zerk will be more effective against casters.  And of course, if a caster, especially a PBAOE or lifetapper, pops MOC, then well...<br>
<br>
In 1v1 versus archers or melees, however, it's wonderful: it works, it also has a &quot;placebo effect&quot; of raising defense, can't be effectively purged since we attack so quickly, and it will defeinately give the advatage, especially against a slow attacker... one fumble on a 5s attacker is 10s of free damage, and we can do a lot in 10 seconds.<br>
<br>
All in all, I like the changes, especially the timer change.  It helps in both PvP and in PvE, with a less effect in RVR unless you're fighting like a dervish and hitting everyone, then if dice go your way, you've just taken 10 seconds of damage away from quite a number of attackers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#000000>(6/23/03 9:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dirty tricks change</span><hr size=1> It's definately an improvement over the old dirty tricks based on it's timer, making it more available, more potential use.<br>
<br>
At the same time compared to frenzy or triple wield it's also much less effective (due to it being a defensive vs MELEE ability) in RvR. <br>
<br>
Dirty tricks is useless vs casters and doesn't help you kill anyone any faster. Frenzy and triple wield work vs all and in all RvR scenarios, helping you do damage faster.<br>
They also work 100% of the time, no 35% chance to proc, from the first hit. And triple wield also confers a defensive melee ability (immune to crits).<br>
<br>
I think they should consider either giving dirty tricks an offensive use OR lengthen the duration to make up for it being a totally defensive ability OR make it also effective vs casters (one idea would be disrupting mastery of concentration just like shield attacks etc) OR make it also a reverse proc so anyone hitting the merc has a chance to fumble at a reduced rate. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A> at: 6/23/03 9:21 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwerraldarkmorn>Gwerral Darkmorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#000000>(6/23/03 9:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=262.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dirty tricks change</span><hr size=1> Overall, I like the changes to dirt.  Like the others have mentioned, it would be really nice if it would last a little bit longer on the target.  Also, a message saying when it successfully lands on a target would help (ie, &quot;You throw dirt at ____&quot; or &quot;A cloud of dirt surrounds ____&quot;) - just something besides the annimation/sound to show it landing. <p>Gwerral Darkmorn<br>
Master Crushing Mercenary<br>
